\title{Skill Repo Sync}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Push local skills to plurigrid/asi repo, remove skills by agreement (with full history purge), and manage .gitignore for local-only skills. Triggers: push skills, sync asi, remove skill from repo, skill repo sync, purge skill.}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Repo Sync}
\p{Manages the flow between local skill directories and the upstream \code{\startverbplurigrid/asi\stopverb} repo.}

\subtree{
\title{Directories}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Upstream}: \code{\startverb/Users/alice/v/asi/skills/\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Local sources}: \code{\startverb~/.claude/skills/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/v/.agents/skills/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/.codex/skills/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/.config/goose/skills/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/.copilot/skills/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/.openhands/skills/\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Standalone}: \code{\startverb~/repos/skills/skill-codex/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/ies/mcp/topos/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb~/v/gay-terminal-colors/\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Operations}
\subtree{
\title{Find what needs pushing}
\p{Use \code{\startverbskill-finder-verifier\stopverb} first:}

\pre{\startverb
python3 ~/.claude/skills/skill-finder-verifier/scripts/finder.py scan
\stopverb}

\p{Skills classified as \code{\startverblocal-only\stopverb} are candidates for pushing.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Push local skills to asi}
\pre{\startverb
cd /Users/alice/v/asi
# Copy from source
cp -r <source>/skill-name skills/skill-name
# Stage, commit, push
git add skills/skill-name
git -c commit.gpgsign=false commit -m "feat: add skill-name"
git push origin main
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Remove a skill by agreement (full purge)}
\p{When a skill must be removed with no trace:}

\pre{\startverb
cd /Users/alice/v/asi
# 1. Purge from all history
/Users/alice/Library/Python/3.9/bin/git-filter-repo --path skills/SKILL-NAME/ --invert-paths --force

# 2. Re-add remote (filter-repo removes it)
git remote add origin https://github.com/plurigrid/asi.git

# 3. Pop any stashed changes
git stash pop  # resolve conflicts if needed

# 4. Add to .gitignore to prevent re-addition
echo "skills/SKILL-NAME/" >> .gitignore
# Add comment: "# Local-only skills (kept on disk, excluded from repo by agreement)"

# 5. Commit and force push
git -c commit.gpgsign=false commit -am "chore: remove SKILL-NAME by agreement"
git push --force origin main
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Keep a skill local-only (no purge needed)}
\p{Just add to \code{\startverb.gitignore\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
echo "skills/skill-name/" >> /Users/alice/v/asi/.gitignore
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Gate (skill-creator rules)}
\p{When pushing skills, review and fix them inline — never report issues without fixing them. skill-creator criteria take priority:}

\ul{
\li{SKILL.md with YAML frontmatter (\code{\startverbname\stopverb}, \code{\startverbdescription\stopverb} with trigger words). No extra fields.}
\li{Under 500 lines. Only context Claude doesn't already have.}
\li{No human-oriented content: no README, prerequisites, pip install, "Learn More", difficulty ratings, estimated times.}
\li{No textbook definitions or standard algorithms Claude already knows.}
\li{No GF(3) trit assignment sections, SDF interleaving, or philosophical decoration.}
\li{Ground all APIs to actual file paths and commands. No aspirational/unimplemented interfaces.}
\li{File must be named \code{\startverbSKILL.md\stopverb}, not \code{\startverbinstructions.md\stopverb} or anything else.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GPG Note}
\p{GPG signing is not available on this machine. Use \code{\startverbgit -c commit.gpgsign=false commit\stopverb} for commits.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Companion Skills}
\ul{
\li{\strong{skill-finder-verifier}: Identifies local-only and modified skills}
\li{\strong{claude-questions-leaderboard}: Track question quality (uses same DuckDB pattern)}
}
}
}